    "title": "The Imperfect Tense",
    "screens": [
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "What is the Imperfect?",
        "content": "The imperfect describes ongoing or habitual past actions, background information, and descriptions in the past. Think of it as 'used to' or 'was doing'."
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Imperfect -AR Endings",
        "content": "Using HABLAR:\n                              \n   ✏️ Exercise: Cuando era niño, ___ mucho. (jugar)",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "yo hablaba",
            "english": "I used to speak / was speaking"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "tú hablabas",
            "english": "you used to speak"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "él/ella hablaba",
            "english": "he/she used to speak"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "nosotros hablábamos",
            "english": "we used to speak"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "ellos hablaban",
            "english": "they used to speak"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Imperfect -ER/-IR Endings",
        "content": "-ER and -IR share the same endings:\n                              → ellos comían/vivían = they used to eat/live",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "yo comía/vivía",
            "english": "I used to eat/live"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "tú comías/vivías",
            "english": "you used to eat/live"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "él comía/vivía",
            "english": "he used to eat/live"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "nosotros comíamos/vivíamos",
            "english": "we used to eat/live"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "ellos comían/vivían",
            "english": "they used to eat/live"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Only 3 Irregular Verbs!",
        "content": "Great news - only 3 verbs are irregular in imperfect:\n                  \n   ✏️ Exercise: Cuando ___ niño, vivía en México. (ser)",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "SER: era, eras, era, éramos, eran",
            "english": "was/were (essence)"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "IR: iba, ibas, iba, íbamos, iban",
            "english": "was going/used to go"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "VER: veía, veías, veía, veíamos, veían",
            "english": "used to see/was seeing"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
